&reftitle.description;

 public Ds\MapDs\Map::diff
 Ds\Mapmap



  Returns the result of removing all keys from the current instance that are
  present in a given map.



  A \ B = {x ∈ A | x ∉ B}

&reftitle.parameters;


  map



      The map containing the keys to exclude in the resulting map.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


  The result of removing all keys from the current instance that are
  present in a given map.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Ds\Map::diff example


<?php
$a = new \Ds\Map(["a" => 1, "b" => 2, "c" => 3]);
$b = new \Ds\Map(["b" => 4, "c" => 5, "d" => 6]);

var_dump($a->diff($b));
?>


